title: "Wobble: Adaptive KV Cache Quantization"
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using the metadata from this file."
authors:
  - family-names: Mohammed
    given-names: Saleem
type: software
url: "https://github.com/bio-bench/wobble-quant-cache"
repository-code: "https://github.com/bio-bench/wobble-quant-cache"
license: MIT
date-released: "2026-03-31"
version: "0.1.0"
keywords:
  - quantization
  - kv-cache
  - large-language-models
  - transformers
  - adaptive-quantization
abstract: >-
  Adaptive per-dimension KV cache quantization for LLMs.
  Measures which dimensions carry the most information and
  allocates more bits to them, while low-variance "wobble"
  dimensions get fewer. Achieves +0.02% perplexity
  degradation at 3-bit on Gemma-2-2B (effectively lossless)
  and beats KIVI at every bit-width on every model tested.
